    <item>
      <title>Lesson 1: IIIF</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/1-iiif/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 02:01:58 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/1-iiif/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#39;callout callout-custom&#39; style=&#39;background-color:rgb(244, 228, 245); border: 1px dotted #d340e0;&#39;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    📚 &lt;u&gt;Lesson plan&lt;/u&gt;&#xA;    &lt;br /&gt;&#xA;    This lesson introduces core concepts associated with the international image interoperability framework (IIIF)&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;nav class=&#34;toc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;details open&gt;&#xA;    &lt;summary&gt;Contents&lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;    &lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#whats-iiif&#34;&gt;What&amp;rsquo;s IIIF?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#whats-the-problem&#34;&gt;What&amp;rsquo;s the problem?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#how-does-iiif-work&#34;&gt;How does IIIF work?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#the-iiif-manifest&#34;&gt;The IIIF Manifest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#viewers&#34;&gt;Viewers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#iiif-tools&#34;&gt;IIIF Tools&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#annotations&#34;&gt;Annotations&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#liiive&#34;&gt;Liiive&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;whats-iiif&#34;&gt;What&amp;rsquo;s IIIF?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;(pronounced &amp;ldquo;triple-eye-eff&amp;rdquo;)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;International Image Interoperability Framework&lt;/strong&gt;, or IIIF for short, is an image sharing protocol commonly used by libraries and museums. Even a basic understanding of it will unlock a vast, rich world of IIIF-enabled materials. Let&amp;rsquo;s get into it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Lesson 2: Georeferencing</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/2-georeferencing/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 02:01:58 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/2-georeferencing/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#39;callout callout-custom&#39; style=&#39;background-color:rgb(244, 228, 245); border: 1px dotted #d340e0;&#39;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    📚 &lt;u&gt;Lesson plan&lt;/u&gt;&#xA;    &lt;br /&gt;&#xA;    This lesson introduces core concepts associated with georeferencing&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;nav class=&#34;toc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;details open&gt;&#xA;    &lt;summary&gt;Contents&lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;    &lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#georeferencing&#34;&gt;Georeferencing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#why-georeference&#34;&gt;Why georeference?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#georeferencing-methods&#34;&gt;Georeferencing methods&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#iiif-review&#34;&gt;IIIF review&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#iiif-powered-georeferencing&#34;&gt;IIIF-powered georeferencing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#finding-iiif-maps&#34;&gt;Finding IIIF maps&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;georeferencing&#34;&gt;Georeferencing&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Georeferencing&#34;&gt;Georeferencing&lt;/a&gt; describes the process of overlaying scanned map images on their real-world locations. While this practice emerged as a way of transforming aerial and satellite photography into spatial data, it&amp;rsquo;s commonly used to place historic maps on modern ones and compare change over time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Lesson 3: Allmaps</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/3-allmaps/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 02:01:58 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/3-allmaps/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#39;callout callout-custom&#39; style=&#39;background-color:rgb(244, 228, 245); border: 1px dotted #d340e0;&#39;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    📚 &lt;u&gt;Lesson plan&lt;/u&gt;&#xA;    &lt;br /&gt;&#xA;    In this lesson, we&amp;#39;ll get hands-on experience georeferencing maps in Allmaps, including an overview of the georeferencing workflow&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;nav class=&#34;toc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;details open&gt;&#xA;    &lt;summary&gt;Contents&lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;    &lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#allmaps-editor&#34;&gt;Allmaps Editor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#masking&#34;&gt;Masking&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#ground-control-points&#34;&gt;Ground control points&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#what-is-this-doing&#34;&gt;What is this doing?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#example-georeference-annotation&#34;&gt;Example georeference annotation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;allmaps-editor&#34;&gt;Allmaps Editor&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you haven&amp;rsquo;t already, launch the Allmaps Editor by going to &lt;a href=&#34;https://editor.allmaps.org&#34;&gt;editor.allmaps.org&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can choose a map by either:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Entering a &lt;strong&gt;IIIF Manifest URL&lt;/strong&gt; in the text box at the top of the page&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Scrolling down to find a map in one of the highlighted collections&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../../images/georef_nz1_start.png&#34; alt=&#34;Start screen of the Allmaps Editor&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Lesson 4: Doing more with Allmaps</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/4-more/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 02:01:58 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/4-more/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#39;callout callout-custom&#39; style=&#39;background-color:rgb(244, 228, 245); border: 1px dotted #d340e0;&#39;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    📚 &lt;u&gt;Lesson plan&lt;/u&gt;&#xA;    &lt;br /&gt;&#xA;    This lesson introduces some additional applications in the Allmaps application, including Viewer, as well as other transformation types. We&amp;#39;ll also work together to make a map mosaic of urban atlases that we can all view at the end of the workshop.&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;nav class=&#34;toc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;details open&gt;&#xA;    &lt;summary&gt;Contents&lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;    &lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#allmaps-viewer&#34;&gt;Allmaps Viewer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#viewing-mosaiqued-atlases&#34;&gt;Viewing mosaiqued atlases&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#changing-the-transformation-algorithm&#34;&gt;Changing the transformation algorithm&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#putting-it-all-together&#34;&gt;Putting it all together&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#open-the-atlas&#34;&gt;Open the atlas&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#claim-a-plate&#34;&gt;Claim a plate&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#georeference&#34;&gt;Georeference&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#view-and-refine&#34;&gt;View and refine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#using-xyz-tiles-in-qgis&#34;&gt;Using XYZ tiles in QGIS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#more-you-can-do&#34;&gt;More you can do&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;allmaps-viewer&#34;&gt;Allmaps Viewer&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://viewer.allmaps.org&#34;&gt;Allmaps Viewer&lt;/a&gt; is used to view georeferenced maps in Allmaps. Similar to the &lt;code&gt;Results&lt;/code&gt; tab in the Editor, you can see the map overlaid on a web map.&#xA;The Viewer also includes additional tools that let you customize the appearance and functionality of your map.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
